Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) is a list of standardized identifiers for publicly known computer vulnerabilities. CVE is designed to cataloge and standardize the names for all publicly known vulnerabilities and exposures through the use of a unique identifier which may be used to refer to a specific vulnerability unambiguously.

